{"id":14880731,"mediaExerciseId":"121ffb27-17a4-4314-99fa-2a13c88035ef","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"1","chapterTitle":"Introduction To Corporate Finance","groupId":612258,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":19,"solutions":[{"id":5895060,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine the advantages and disadvantages of changing the company organization from a sole proprietorship to an LLC.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define some terms.\n\n- **Sole proprietorship** is a business structure owned by an individual who exclusively owns all assets and profits of the business.\n\n- **Limited Liability Company or LLC** is a type legal entity created by law whereby the owners are not personally liable for the debts of the company.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The **advantages** of changing the company organization from a sole proprietorship to an LLC are:\n\n- limited liability of the owners which means they are not personally liable for company's debts\n- owners are not taxed as a separate business entity\n**bold text**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/16/ea63fe98cd460c1c931e187d5fac2064/34d4f2f8ed8fd3254c0c51871af75726/lateximg_large.png","width":1027},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/16/ea63fe98cd460c1c931e187d5fac2064/34d4f2f8ed8fd3254c0c51871af75726/lateximg.png","width":515}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The **disadvantages** of changing the company organization from a sole proprietorship to an LLC are:\n\n- difficult and expensive to form\n- ownership is hard to transfer","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":179,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/16/ea63fe98cd460c1c931e187d5fac2064/4a407ddc711cd7c9101511c4f4505aa9/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/16/ea63fe98cd460c1c931e187d5fac2064/4a407ddc711cd7c9101511c4f4505aa9/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"c984fb9a-2318-4ed2-8905-12b49d926f0a","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880732,"exerciseName":"2","page":19,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"be22d758-2fc3-463a-898c-f2e52972d886","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-minicase-questions-2-be22d758-2fc3-463a-898c-f2e52972d886"},{"id":14880733,"exerciseName":"3","page":19,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"4275ba69-e6d6-4d55-b663-0aef24e8425e","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-minicase-questions-3-4275ba69-e6d6-4d55-b663-0aef24e8425e"}],